Further, the aforementioned analysis serves as a fundamental basis for elucidating the potential photocatalytic mechanism for the Z-scheme CQDs@WS2/PANI ternary nanocomposite system, as well as the plausible pathway for the transfer of photo-induced charges. The dynamic charge transfer and band bending at heterogeneous junction interfaces are substantially impacted by the positioning of energy levels. In the case of PANI, the conduction band (CB) was located at −1.66 ​eV, possesses the capability to reduce molecular oxygen (O2) to superoxide radicals (•O2
                        −), which exists at a lower energy state (−0.33 ​eV). In contrast, the valence band (VB) of WS2 can react with hydroxide ions (OH−) to generate hydroxyl radicals (•OH), a reaction favoured by the more positive potential of OH−/•OH at approximately +1.99 ​eV(Fig. 14
                        ) [80].
